$ ./get_work.py -h
usage: get_work.py [-h] [-f] [-c CORES] [-w WORKUNITS] [-t TYPE] [-m MINIMUM]
                   [-v] [-o OUTPUT]

optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  -f, --force           Get new work even if you already have more than the
                        configured minimum amount
  -c CORES, --cores CORES
                        Number of workers to collect work for
  -w WORKUNITS, --workunits WORKUNITS
                        Number of workunits to collect work for each core/
                        worker
  -t TYPE, --type TYPE  work type identifier id.
  -m MINIMUM, --minimum MINIMUM
                        minimum number of workunits in target file
  -v, --verbose         verbose
  -o OUTPUT, --output OUTPUT
                        specify an output file
